@node Usage

The GUI
-------

The pagegadget swaps from Tools-Menu to Hotkey editor. You can use the [TAB] key
to swap between both listviews.

Listview displaying the entries from either Tools-Menu or Hotkey functions. You can
walk trough the list with the cursor keys. To jump to the top of the listview press
[Home] and to jump to the buttom use [End] key.


Add		- add a new command to the listview. The new entry will be placed
		  below the cursor.
Add Parent	- adds a submenu title.
Add Submenu	- adds the actual submenu entry to a submenu title.
Remove		- removes the selected entry.
Duplicate	- will create a new entry with exactly the same options of the entry
		  where the cursor is placed on.
Up		- the selected entry one position up.
Down		- the selected entry one position down.

To add a seperator line choose a name you like and use in the title stringgadget an
"-", "~" or "_" (without ""), thats it.

Please don't use spaces in drawer nor filenames. I only implement a basic
identification routine to check for arguments.


The Configfile
--------------
T.H.E. creates an ARexx script that will be placed in "REXX:"-drawer. Furthermore the
path to this script will be stored in ENVARC:T.H.E./Scriptname.

The WBStartup
-------------

The Installer script will include the configuration into your WBStartup procedure. If
you changed the location of the central ARexx script "setKeyAndMenu.rexx" @{b}after@{ub}
installation you need to adjust the automatic start by yourself. For AmigaOS 3.9 you
should alter the standard program of the setKeyAndMenu.rexx icon in your WBStartup
drawer to the new path. When using AmigaOS 4.1 you just need to change the path to this
script by the usual SYS:Prefs/WBStartup program.

@endnode

@node arexx
Since v1.1 T.H.E. offers an ARexx host under the name of "T.H.E.". It supports
some commands as will be described below.

1. UNICONIFY

If the T.H.E. window is iconified it will be pop up.


2. ICONIFY

iconify the T.H.E. window.


3. QUIT

will quit T.H.E. @{b}without@{ub} a requester.


4. ACTIVATE

activates the T.H.E. window.


5. FRONT				(v1.3)

window to front.


6. BACK					(v1.3)

window to back.
@endnode

